        		</a>
			</div>
  		</div>
	</nav>

	<h3 align="center">Find A Recipe</h3>
	<div class="container" id="main-div">
		<p id="userName">
		</p>
		<h5><strong> Give us in a word or two what you'd like to eat today, and we'll match you with a recipe. </strong></h5>
		<input id="query" type="text" placeholder="i.e. burger, sandwich, ...">
	</br></br>
		<h5> Note: the following questions are all optional. </h5>
		<h5> How difficult do you want your meal to be to create? If you don't care you can leave it at "normal".</h5>
		<label class="radio-inline"><input type="radio" name="diff" value="0">Easy</label>
		<label class="radio-inline"><input checked type="radio" name="diff" value="1">Normal</label>
		<label class="radio-inline"><input type="radio" name="diff" value="2">Hard</label>
		<h5> Do you want a specific cuisine today? </h5>
		<input id="cuisine" type="text" placeholder="i.e. american, indian, ...">
		<h5> Do you want a calorie limit? If so, put in the number of calories you'd like to keep the meal to.</h5>
		<input id="calories" type="text" placeholder="i.e. 1200">
		<h5> Any cravings for specific ingredients? You can put in multiple with commas in between. </h5>
		<input id="ingredients" type="text" placeholder="i.e. lettuce, pickles, ...">
		<div class="wrapper" id="padding123">
			<button id="go" type="button" class="btn btn-success">Go!</button>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div align="center" id="afterContainer"></div>
	<div align="center" id="nextRecipe">
		<div id="paddingTest">
			<button id="nextRecipeButton" align="center" display="none" type="button" class="btn btn-default">
				Not quite right? Click me for another recipe!
			</button>
		</div>
		<div>
			<button id="startOver" align="center" display="none" type="button" class="btn btn-warning">
				Start Over
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>

	<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery.js"></script>
	<script src="/js/bootstrap.js"></script>
	<script src="/js/mealC.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
